SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1046
By Pody
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Liz Reese for her
essential work as executive director of Brooks
House.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in honoring a
lady who has earned the respect and gratitude of her community through her vital work with
women and children in need of assistance; and
WHEREAS, Liz Reese makes a positive difference in the lives of the women and
children residing at Lebanon's Brooks House, where she has adroitly served as executive
director since March 2007; and
WHEREAS, for many years, Ms. Reese has provided housing and resources to women
and children who are seeking a "hand up not a hand out," thus fulfilling her personal mission of
helping our most vulnerable citizens with the compassion of Christ in her heart; and
WHEREAS, her dedicated service to Wilson County and her fellow citizens has been
recognized with numerous awards and accolades, including her receipt of the Resilience Award
from Tennessee Workforce for her work with Hurricane Katrina victims; the 2008 Humanitarian
Award from the Wilson County Civic League; the Governor's Volunteer Award for Wilson
County; and honors from the American Red Cross for her volunteer work during hurricanes
Katrina and Gustav; and
WHEREAS, Liz Reese also gives back to her community through service on the Board
of Directors of the Lebanon Housing Authority and the Board of Trustees of University Medical
Center; and
WHEREAS, she previously served on the Board of Directors of Habitat for Humanity of
Wilson County and was a member of Leadership Wilson, Class of 2008; and
SJR1046
016978
- 1 -

WHEREAS, a lady of diverse professional experience, Ms. Reese has certainly excelled
in her role as executive director of Brooks House, and she is most worthy of our approbation;
now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Liz Reese for her essential
work at Brooks House, praise her commitment to the health and welfare of the women and
children she so compassionately serves, and extend to her our best wishes for much continued
success and happiness.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
